  meanings
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "A simulation, by whatever means, of a military operation involving two or more opposing forces using rules, data, and procedures designed to depict an actual or assumed real-life situation."
        entry
          definition "A game that simulates or represents a military operation."
      partOfSpeech noun
      synonyms ("military exercise" "training exercise")
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "To run a military simulation of this kind."
      partOfSpeech verb
